  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A governing requirement mandates experimental-validation as the required verification method for hemolysis QoI acceptance. The supporting validation result, however, was generated by a high-fidelity numerical simulation activity that the assessment narrative characterises as 'functionally equivalent to bench-top measurement given the convergence and mesh-independence evidence obtained.' The structured activity record carries activityType 'numerical-simulation', creating an inference-method mismatch with the requirement's requiredVerificationMethod field while the prose obscures the discrepancy.",
