      "name": "Hemolysis index QoI validation — high-fidelity CFD sweep",
      "description": "Predicted hemolysis index values across all 5 flow-speed operating points. The assessment team concluded that the mesh-independent, turbulence-resolved CFD solution with Monte Carlo UQ provides evidence of model adequacy that is, in practice, as informative as a physical bench experiment for this geometry. All predicted values fell below the clinical hemolysis threshold with a 95 % confidence interval margin of 18 %.",
      "wasGeneratedBy": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/cfd-hemolysis-simulation-sweep",
        "type": "Activity",
        "activityType": "numerical-simulation",
        "name": "High-fidelity CFD hemolysis simulation sweep",
        "description": "Transient, mesh-independent CFD simulation of the FDA generic centrifugal pump across 5 operating points using the modified power-law hemolysis model. Grid convergence index < 1.2 % on hemolysis index. Monte Carlo sampling (N=5000) over inlet flow rate, rotational speed, and blood viscosity. No physical bench measurements were performed; the numerical evidence is argued to substitute for experimental validation given the maturity of the solver and the prior FDA pump round-robin data."
      }
    }
  ],
