    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the package on the basis that the high-fidelity CFD simulation sweep, supported by Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification and GCI-verified mesh independence, provides evidence of hemolysis model adequacy that the team judged to be functionally equivalent to bench-top experimental validation for this well-characterised FDA benchmark geometry. The governing requirement specifies experimental-validation as the required verification method; however, the team concluded that the numerical simulation evidence, combined with prior FDA round-robin corroboration, satisfies the intent of the requirement. Multiple credibility factors remain below required levels and six factors are unassessed, but the team determined residual gaps are acceptable given the conservative hemolysis threshold margin of 18 %.",
